==================================================
Name	        : DeskWid
version	        : 0.1
Git             : https://github.com/jayrambhia/DeskWid
compatibility   : Linux (Ubuntu, Mint tested)

Credits :   The Python-Twitter Developers for twitter library, BeautifulSoup library,
            and many others from whom I learned Pytohn, multithreading, pygtk, and my
            friends who have encouraged me all this time.

It's a Desktop Widget for twitter, imdb, and sticky notes

To use this GUI, you need your consumer key, consumer secret, access tokey key, and access token secret.
Get all these from https://dev.twitter.com/
Enter all of the above mentioned keys in the script.

Requirements:
    BeautifulSoup library
    Twitter library(included)
    imdb library(included)
    pygtk 2.0 or greater
    gtk
    oauth2
    mechanize library
    gdbm library

$ python deskwid.py

commands:
    Tweet:  \t<space><your tweet> 
            \t Hey! Tweeting using @deskwid #python!
            
    timeline:   \timeline
    
                \timeline<space><int> int is timeinterval in minutes
        eg:     \timeline 5
        
                \timeline --stop
                    
    IMDb:   \imdb<space><movie name>
      eg:   \imdb the dark knight
      
    proxy:  --proxy<space>http://username:password@proxy:port
        eg: --proxy http://jayrambhia:jayrambhia@10.1.9.36:8080
            --proxy http://10.1.9.36:8080
            
            --proxy<space>https://username:password@proxy:port
        eg: --proxy https://jayrambhia:jayrambhia@10.1.9.36:8080
            --proxy https://10.1.9.36:8080
            
            --proxy none
            
    consumer key        --consumer_key<space><your consumer key>
    consumer secret     --consumer_secret<space><youe consumer secret>
    access token key    --access_token_key<space><you access token key>
    access token secret --access_token_secret<space><your access token secret>

    **  Restart the application after changing proxy settings and changing/adding
        consumer keys, consumer secret, etc to bring in the changes.
